article.headline: E. Washington 91, Cascade 59
article.story: CHENEY, Wash. (AP) -- Adris DeLeon came off the bench to score 15 points Friday night as Eastern Washington cruised past Cascade College 91-59. Kellen Williams added 14 points and nine rebounds for the Eagles (4-8), who hit a school-record 16 3-pointers and had seven players score in double figures against the NAIA Thunderbirds (5-5). Erving Adams scored a game-high 22 points for Cascade. A pair of free throws by Cascade's Tayo Cotton brought the Thunderbirds within 18-14 early in the game before the Eagles, of the Big Sky Conference, pulled away. Milan Stanojevic finished a 12-2 Eastern burst with four consecutive free throws, courtesy of two Cascade technical fouls, as the Eagles opened up a 30-16 lead with 10:40 remaining in the first half. EWU closed the first half with a 18-4 run to take a 60-30 halftime edge. Cascade never got closer than 24 the rest of the way. Trey Gross and Stanojevic each added 13 points for EWU, which shot 59 percent on 3-point attempts. Brandon Moore had 12 points and nine rebounds and Gary Gibson and Marcus Hinton each chipped in 11 points. Cotton scored 15 for Cascade.
